.TH SIMPLE_SHELL

.SH NAME
SIMPLE_SHELL - A simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH COMMANDS

.TP
.B ls
Display all the directory and files in the current directory.

.B exit
Exit the shell
.B ^D
Exit too.

.SH MODES
 The shell can be used in two different modes, the intercative one and the non-interactive one.

.TP
.B Interactive mode
The shell display a "$" and wait for commandn when the command is done the shell restart the process.

Exemples:
.EX
$ ./hsh
#cisfun$ ls
file1 file2 file3 file4 directory1/
#cisfun$
.EE 

.TP
.B Non-interactive mode
The shell display only the result of the command without a prompt (Ex : echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh)

Exemples:
.EX
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
file1 directory1/ file2
$
.EE

